						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/South-Africa-A-shot-in-the-arm-for-exceptional-women-scientists" title="South Africa: A shot in the arm for exceptional women scientists" alt="link">South Africa: A shot in the arm for exceptional women scientists</a></h2>

	
					<p>Kgaogelo Amanda Maswanganye is one of the five inaugural recipients of the L'Oréal and Unesco Regional Fellowships for Women in Science in sub-Saharan Africa. Born in Limpopo, Maswanganye is one of two South African women to be awarded a fellowship towards the completion of their PhD studies. She is based at the University of Pretoria, where she tutors in molecular biology and is &quot;concentrating on the grasslands of SA, which are fast disappearing, and its species such as dassies and mice and their distribution. (Source: All Africa, 19 April 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/South-Africa-A-shot-in-the-arm-for-exceptional-women-scientists">Read more...</a>
