						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Cuban-scientist-wins-U.S.-based-environmental-prize" title="Cuban scientist wins U.S.-based environmental prize" alt="link">Cuban scientist wins U.S.-based environmental prize</a></h2>

	
					<p>A scientist who says that the key to Cuba's agricultural future lies in its agrarian past has become the first Cuban to win a U.S.-based Goldman Environmental Prize, the world's biggest award for grassroots environmentalism. Humberto Rios, 46, was announced as a prize winner on April 19 in San Francisco along with five other activists from around the world. They will each receive $150,000, a huge sum in Cuba where the average annual salary is equivalent to $240. Rios won the prize for his work on promoting a return to more traditional farming techniques focusing on seed diversity, crop rotation and the use of organic pest control and fertilizers to both increase crops and improve the communist-led island's environment. (Source: Reuters, 19 April 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Cuban-scientist-wins-U.S.-based-environmental-prize">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
