						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Climate-models-to-predict-African-disease-outbreak" title="Climate models to predict African disease outbreak" alt="link">Climate models to predict African disease outbreak</a></h2>

	
					<p>African and European researchers are to join forces in a new project that is to use climate modelling to predict outbreaks of diseases in Senegal, Ghana and Malawi. In the new project, researchers across 13 European and African research institutes are set to work together to integrate data from climate modelling and disease forecasting systems to predict the likelihood of an epidemic up to six months in advance. The research, funded by the EC is set to focus on climate and disease in Senegal, Ghana and Malawi and aims to give decision makers the necessary time to deploy intervention methods to help prevent large scale spread of diseases such as Rift Valley Fever and malaria. (Source: afrol News, 16 April 2010)</p>
							<p><span class="date">26/04/2010</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Climate-models-to-predict-African-disease-outbreak">Read more...</a>
